    "The study underscores the importance of investigating the validity for all tested LLMs, as the authors conclude that larger, instruction-tuned models reach better results in the construct validity study.",
    "R5b (Validity of Test Translations) With only two reports taking into account multilingual scenarios, requirement R5b is the least explored aspect among the specified requirements.",
    "Stevenson et al. (2022) include a translation of test answers to compare test scores of English and Dutch versions, which were separately administered to GPT-3 and a Dutch human group.",
    "The translation procedure was not further specified and as such, the comparability of both tests is hard to verify.",
    "In contrast, Pellert et al."
